Class ComplexExpression

java.lang.Object
models.ComplexExpression
Direct Known Subclasses:
AdditionExpression, DivisionExpression, MultiplicationExpression, SubtractionExpression
public abstract class ComplexExpression extends Object
Abstract class representing an arithmetic expression involving complex numbers.

The class follows the Template Method Design Pattern, where the method execute() implements a general algorithm that sequentially applies operations on complex numbers, delegating the actual operation to the subclass through the executeOneOperation(ComplexNumber, ComplexNumber) method.

  • Method Details

    • execute

      public ComplexNumber execute()
      Executes the complex expression by sequentially applying the specified operation on all complex numbers provided as arguments.

      This method starts with the first complex number in the array and applies the operation pairwise on the remaining numbers.

      Returns:
      the result of the complex expression after applying the operatios on all provided complex numbers
